    "17-18.• The role of quark and lepton observables to mutually constrain each other is visible in the results in Table 1 and in Fig. 22.The above results are relevant for the NP searches at the new facilities planned within the future strategy for particle physics.",
    "A B q → V local form factorsWe use the standard parametrization of the B q → V (q = d, s, V = K *, ϕ) matrix elements of local currents in terms of form factors: ⟨V (p ′, ϵ)|sσ µν q ν (1 + γ⟨V (p ′, ϵ)|sγ µ (1 -γ 5)b|B q (p)⟩ = ϵ µναβ ϵ * ν p α p ′β 2V (q 2) m Bq + m V -i ϵ * µ (m Bq + m V)A 1 (q 2) -(ϵ * • q)(p + p ′) µ A 2 (q 2) m Bq + m V -(ϵ * • q) 2m V q 2 A 3 (q 2) -A 0 (q 2) q µ, (A.1)5)b|B q (p)⟩ = iϵ µναβ ϵ * ν p α p ′β 2 T 1 (q 2) + ϵ * µ (m 2 Bq -m 2 V) -(ϵ * • q)(p + p ′) µ T 2 (q 2) +(ϵ * • q) q µ - q 2 m 2 Bq -m 2 V (p + p ′) µ T 3 (q 2), (A.2)with q = p -p ′ and ϵ the V polarization vector.",
    "The form factors are not all independent: A 3 is given byA 3 (q 2) = m Bq + m V 2m V A 1 (q 2) - m Bq -m V 2m V A 2 (q 2) (A.3)with A 3 (0) = A 0 (0).",
